quran[20]{c,v,t,f}:
  76,6,"This will be a gushing spring{1} wherefrom Allah's servants{2} shall drink wine, a spring from which they will take out channels wherever they wish.{3}",1:[That is, it will],2:[not be camphor-mixed],3:[water but a]
  76,7,"These will be the ones who fulfil their vows{1} and dread the Day whose woe shall be spread far and wide;",1:[One meaning of fulfilling the vow is that one should]
  76,8,"those who, for the love of Him,{1} feed the needy, and the orphan, and the captive,{2}",1:[Most of the commentators hold],2:[the view that the]
  76,9,"(saying):{1} “We feed you only for Allah's sake; we do not seek of you any recompense or thanks,{2}",1:[Although feeding a poor man is],2:[in itself a great virtue,]
  76,10,"we fear from our Lord a Day that shall be long and distressful.”"
  76,11,"So Allah shall guard them against the woe of that Day, and will procure them freshness and joy,{1}",1:[Radiance and joy: radiance of the face and joy of the]
  76,12,"and will reward them for their steadfastness{1} with Paradise and robes of silk.",1:[Here the word sabr (patience) has been used in a very comprehensive sense. The whole worldly life of the righteous believers in fact has been described as a life of patience. From the time a man attains discretion]
  76,13,"There they will recline on elevated couches and will be subjected neither to the burning heat of the sun nor to bitter cold."
  76,14,"The shades of Paradise will bend over them, and its fruits will be brought within their easy reach;"
  76,15,"and there shall be passed around them vessels of silver{1} and goblets of crystal,{2}",1:[According to  (Surah Az-Zukhruf:Ayat 71), vessels of],2:[Ayat 71), vessels of]
  76,16,"goblets bright as crystal but made of silver, filled to exact measure.{1}",1:[“In due measure”: filled accurately according to the]
  76,17,"Therein they shall be served a cup flavoured with ginger,"
  76,18,"drawn from a spring (in Paradise) called Salsabil.{1}",1:[This is to suit the taste of the Arabs who liked the wine]
  76,19,"There boys of everlasting youth shall go about attending them: when you see them, you would think that they are scattered pearls.{1}",1:[For explanation, see(Surah As-Saaffat: E.N. 26)]
  76,20,"Whitherto you look around, you will see an abundance of bliss and the glories of a great kingdom.{1}",1:[Even if a person might have lived a pauper in the]
  76,21,"They [i.e., the virtuous] shall be attired in garments of fine green silk and rich brocade{1} and will be adorned with bracelets of silver.{2} Their Lord will give them a pure wine to drink.{3}",1:[The same theme],2:[has been],3:[expressed in]
  76,22,"Behold, this is your recompense and your endeavour has been appreciated.{1}",1:[In the original, kana sayu kum mashkura: “your]
  76,23,"(O Prophet), indeed We have revealed the Qur'an to you in portions.{1}",1:[Though the addressee here apparently is the Prophet]
  76,24,"So persevere with the command of your Lord{1} and do not pay any heed to the wicked and the unbelieving,{2}",1:[“Be patient”:Face patiently the hardships and],2:[Face patiently the hardships and]
  76,25,"and remember the name of your Lord, morning and evening;"
